isReadyForJoin

public boolean isReadyForJoin()
Returns true if the minimal requirements of this Authenticator have been satisfied and it is ready for submission to MembershipService.join(Authenticator).

Membership services may use this method in a variety of ways. The simplest (and most common) usage is to ensure that all of the required authentication parameters have acceptable (not necessarily correct) values. Some authenticators may behave asynchronously and this method can be used to determine if the authentication process has completed.

In all cases Authenticator.isReadyForJoin() should be lower cost than calling MembershipService.join(Authenticator).

This method provides no distinction between incomplete authentication and failed authentication.

Specified by:
isReadyForJoin in interface Authenticator
Returns:
true if the authenticator is "complete" and ready for submitting to MembershipService.join(Authenticator), otherwise false.
See Also:
MembershipService.join(Authenticator)
